# pxcp

Peter's Extended Copy Tool for FreeBSD, Linux & MacOS (and Solaris in the future)

Supports copying and mirroring file trees including attributes, timestamps, ACLs, Extended Attributes,
File Flags.


AUTHOR

  Peter Eriksson <pen@lysator.liu.se>


Handles various ACLs:

 POSIX (Linux, FreeBSD)
 ZFS (FreeBSD)
 NFS4 (all, including on Linux)
 EXTENDED (MacOS)


USAGE:
  ./pxcp [options] <src> <dst>

Options:
  -a    Archive mode (enables g,o,r,t,A,F,X options)
  -d    Set debugging output level
  -e    Only copy to existing targets
  -f    Force updates
  -g    Copy object group
  -h    Display usage information
  -i    Ignore non-fatal errors and continue
  -m    Only copy metadata
  -n    Enable dry-run mode
  -o    Copy object owner
  -p    Prune removed objects
  -r    Enable recursion
  -s    Set sync mode
  -t    Copy modfication times
  -v    Set verbosity level
  -w    Display warnings/notices
  -x    Do not cross filesystems
  -A    Copy ACLs
  -F    Copy file flags
  -M    Use mmap(2)
  -S    Print stats summary
  -X    Copy Extended Attributes

All options may optionally take a numeric argument.


EXAMPLES:
	# pxcp -vap src-dir dst-dir
	Verbose, Archive, and Prune (ie, mirror src-dir to dst-dir)

	# pxdp -vam -t0 src-dir dst-dir
	Verbose, Archive, Metadata only (do not touch file contents), disable clone timestamps
